common jargon that'll prepare you for whenever you're working with AWS IoT

3
00:00:08.086 --> 00:00:11.133
interacting with others who have some experience with it or even just

4
00:00:11.133 --> 00:00:13.978
trying to get through the AWS documentation.

5
00:00:13.978 --> 00:00:16.379
So let's really quickly take a look at a few terms,

6
00:00:16.379 --> 00:00:19.542
starting with the AWS IoT Core.

7
00:00:19.542 --> 00:00:21.557
So what is this AWS IoT Core?

8
00:00:21.557 --> 00:00:21.899
Well,

9
00:00:21.899 --> 00:00:25.971
it includes everything from the IoT Device Gateway to the authentication

10
00:00:25.971 --> 00:00:29.983
and authorization portions of the IoT systems in AWS,

11
00:00:29.983 --> 00:00:33.529
also the Thing Registry where we go and actually register things,

