00:00:58.914 --> 00:01:00.953
I'll go into more detail on some of these bottom

22
00:01:00.953 --> 00:01:03.508
level services in the next sections.

23
00:01:03.508 --> 00:01:08.519
Now in addition to the AWS IoT Core, the words AWS IoT Device Management,

24
00:01:08.519 --> 00:01:11.709
or IoT Device Management, are thrown around a lot too.

25
00:01:11.709 --> 00:01:14.549
Now this essentially just means a few overlapping

26
00:01:14.549 --> 00:01:16.475
characteristics of IoT Core itself.

27
00:01:16.475 --> 00:01:18.940
And this includes things like the Thing Registry,

28
00:01:18.940 --> 00:01:22.064
the Fleet Indexing Service, the Jobs Service,

29
00:01:22.064 --> 00:01:23.165
device logging,

30
00:01:23.165 --> 00:01:27.600
so essentially the logs that are actually generated from our IoT things,

31
00:01:27.600 --> 00:01:29.107
also thing attributes,

32
00:01:29.107 --> 00:01:32.979
both those searchable and non-searchable attributes that I mentioned earlier,

33
00:01:32.979 --> 00:01:34.670
and also thing groups and types,

34
00:01:34.670 --> 00:01:36.754
which are helpful to keep track of all those different

35
00:01:36.754 --> 00:01:38.878
things that we have inside of our account.

36
00:01:38.878 --> 00:01:41.428
So hopefully this will dispel some of the marketing jargon

37
00:01:41.428 --> 00:01:44.375
and you can dive into this knowing what exactly is being

38
00:01:44.375 --> 00:01:46.483
talked about with these two terms.

39
00:01:46.483 --> 00:01:47.616
But now that I've talked about some of this jargon,

40
00:01:47.616 --> 00:01:52.655
